The '''Republican Party of India (Athawale)''' is a [[political party]] in India. The party is a splinter group of the [[Republican Party of India]] and has its roots in the [[Scheduled Castes Federation]] led by [[B. R. Ambedkar]]. The president of the party is [[Ramdas Athawale]].

==History==

Ramdas Athawale was member of the [[Maharashtra Legislative Council]] from 1990 to 1995 and a cabinet member in the [[Government of Maharashtra]]. Subsequently, he was elected to the [[Parliament of India]], representing [[Mumbai North Central (Lok Sabha constituency)|Mumbai North Central]] in the [[12th Lok Sabha]] between 1998-99 and the [[Pandharpur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Pandharpur constituency]] from 1999 to 2004.{{cn|date=April 2018}}

After the 2004 election, it had a small representation in the [[Lok Sabha]] and was a constituent of the ruling [[United Progressive Alliance]]. Its presence is limited to [[Maharashtra]].

All factions of the RPI except [[Prakash Yashwant Ambedkar|Prakash Ambedkar]]'s [[Bharipa Bahujan Mahasangh]] have reunited to form a [[Republican Party of India (United)]].<ref>{{cite news|title=The two Ambedkarite parties, the Republican Party of India led by Ramdas Athawale and the Bharipa Bahujan Mahasangh led by Prakash Ambedkar|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/mumbai/ambedkarites-find-it-hard-to-stay-afloat/}}</ref>

In 2011, the party aligned itself with the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]-led [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Who are Modi's 26 allies in the NDA?|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/column/ls-election-sheela-says-who-are-modis-26-allies-in-the-nda/20140505.htm|date=5 May 2014|access-date=5 April 2016}}</ref>

Rakhi Sawant resigned from Rashtriya Aam Party and joined Republican Party of India (A) in June 2014 and expressed her desire to work for [[Dalit|dalits]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/mumbai/rakhi-sawant-wants-to-join-rpi/|title=Rakhi Sawant wants to join RPI|date=21 June 2014|publisher= ELECTION COMMISSION OF INDIA, GENERAL ELECTION TO LOK SABHA TRENDS & RESULT 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abplive.in/india/2014/06/28/article352666.ece/Rakhi-Sawant-joins-RPI?id=352666#.U651I5SSx1Y|title=Rakhi Sawant joins RPI|date=28 June 2014|publisher=|accessdate=16 July 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160910085656/http://www.abplive.in/india/2014/06/28/article352666.ece/Rakhi-Sawant-joins-RPI?id=352666#.U651I5SSx1Y|archivedate=10 September 2016|df=}}</ref> Rakhi serves as party's state vice-president and president of woman wing.<ref>[http://news.webindia123.com/news/Articles/India/20140621/2411873.html Rakhi Sawant express her desire to join RPI]. News.webindia123.com (21 June 2014). Retrieved on 2016-11-28.</ref>

In September 2015, the RPI(A) was one of 16 parties in Maharashtra to lose its registration for not submitting audited balance sheets and IT return documents since 2005. Thus they have lost their official election symbols.<ref>{{cite news|title=16 political parties lose election symbols in the absence of balance sheets|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/16-political-parties-lose-election-symbols-in-the-absence-of-balance-sheets/articleshow/49158818.cms|date=29 September 2015|access-date=5 April 2016}}</ref>

Athawale is only member in [[Member of Parliament, Rajya Sabha|Member of Parliament in Upper House]] of the Indian parliament. He is currently Minister of State for [[Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment|Social Justice and Empowerment]] Department with Disability Affairs from July 2016 in [[Modi ministry|Narendra Modi ministry]].{{cn|date=April 2018}}

